Package: durumGEAr
Type: Package
Title: Confound-Aware Genotype-Environment Association Modelling for
        Genebank Accessions
Version: 1.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Sabri", "Youssef", email = "youssef.sabri@iav.ac.ma", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Zakaria", "Kehel", role = "ths")
    )
Description: A methodology package for honest genotype-environment association
    (GEA) modelling of plant genetic resources data, developed on a durum wheat
    (Triticum turgidum ssp. durum) genebank collection. The package encapsulates
    a defensible statistical workflow: collapsing pseudoreplicated site-level
    rows to independent effective units (Hurlbert, 1984), spatial-block and
    leave-one-country-out cross-validation (Roberts et al., 2017), fold-safe
    residualization to separate genuine within-country climate signal from
    geographic-identity confounding, and permutation-based driver analysis.
    Function naming and structure follow the conventions of the 'icardaFIGSr'
    package. The workflow demonstrates how a naive predictive score can be an
    artifact of spatial confounding, and how to recover the transferable signal
    underneath it.
